\begin_layout Standard
6.
 Stock & Watson 6.9 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
For omitted variable bias to occur, two conditions must be true: 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1}$
\end_inset

 (the included regressor) is correlated with the omitted variable, and the
 omitted variable is a determinant of the dependent variable.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{2}$
\end_inset

 are uncorrelated, the estimator of 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{1}$
\end_inset

 does not suffer from omitted variable bias.
 
\end_layout

